questions.prompt: An aubade is defined as a morning song. What contrasting and complementary term has been used for evening music, such as to describe Mozart's Eine kleine Nachtmusik or his work commissioned for the wedding of Marie Elisabeth Haffner?

What did the disciple Judas give to Jesus in the Garden of Gethsemane following the Last Supper, as famously depicted in multiple works of art?
All living members of the taxonomic order of animals known as Proboscidea are known commonly as what?
